#Network Devices 

What is a Network?


To better understand the role of networks in the computing world, is to understand the roles of transportation in human lifes. 
Same responsibilities with extra powers. 
A computer network is a digital telecommunications network which allows nodes to share resources. 
By nodes we mean a bunch of different networking devices which encompass mainly routers, hubs, switches and modems. 
In computer networks, computing devices exchange data with each other using connections (data links) between these nodes.
The data links are established over cable media such as wires or optic cables, or wireless media such as Wi-Fi.


It would be better to understand how the network works if we ourselves build a Network to see how it actually happens.

Building a Network.

Client : A client is a device that accesses a service made available by a server.

Servers : A device that provides functions or services for clients. The same device can be a client in some situations, 
and a server in other situations. 

Previously, in the paper we studied switches, routers, modems, and hubs. It would be better if we had a better 
understanding of it now. 

Switch : A switch is better to be taken as a machine that connects several devices in a home network, 
which may comprise various devices like mobile phones, computers, even IOT devices like modern fridge 
or smart TVs. A switch has many network interfaces/ports for end hosts to connect. Though It does not  
provide connectivity between LANs over the internet.

Routers : Routers behave the same way as does a switch but it connects LANs over the internet. 
Its main purpose is to connect devices over the internet and transfer data between devices. 
They are mostly wireless in the modern world, but previously used to be connected through wires.

Modem : Modems are mostly machines that are not existent in the modern world, as they have been integrated 
within the router making it a single machine. Modem connects devices on the network to connect on the internet. 
Alas though their main purpose is to convert analog signals to digital signals which modern machines better understand.  


Firewall : A firewall by the name itself is a wall that protects devices from fire here we mean viruses, worms and malwares. 
A firewall comes in as hardware and as software. A hardware for a better security of a wide machine system.
